<paragraph blockId="89.[264,1323,1574,1721]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
It is very difficult to separate females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sun" authorityYear="2003" box="[785,879,1615,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Phasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kudoi">
<emphasis box="[785,879,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P. kudoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[935,1068,1615,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Phasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurulans">
<emphasis box="[935,950,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[964,1068,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">aurulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sun" authorityName="Sun" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Phasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kudoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Phasia kudoi</emphasis>
Sun
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" box="[595,891,1655,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Phasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurulans">
<emphasis box="[595,791,1655,1680]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Phasia aurulans</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
in lacking a distinct golden yellow pruinose spot on the mesonotum, and in characters of the terminalia.
</paragraph>
